Troubleshooting Tips
nftables rules not loading:

Check syntax with sudo nft -c -f /etc/nftables/anti-ddos.nft
Verify file permissions are correct
Check for conflicting existing rules with sudo nft list ruleset
Nginx rate limiting not working:

Verify zone definitions are before server block
Check Nginx error log: sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log
Test configuration: sudo nginx -t
Python scripts failing:

Verify required libraries are installed
Check file permissions for log access
Run with python3 -u script.py for unbuffered output
Add print statements to debug logic flow
Monitoring not detecting events:

Ensure log files exist and are being written to
Check log file permissions
Verify regex patterns match actual log format
Test parsing functions with sample log lines
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated comprehensive DDoS protection using nftables, Nginx, and automated detection systems. You configured multi-layered defenses including connection rate limiting, suspicious pattern detection, and automated blocking. The integration of Sigma rules provides a standardized approach to threat detection that can be extended to other security scenarios.

Key takeaways:

Defense in depth requires multiple protection layers
Rate limiting is essential for DDoS mitigation
Automated detection reduces response time
Log correlation improves threat visibility
Standardized rules (Sigma) enable consistent detection
